14. ✅ THE PFILE

👉 we were using a text file called the PFILE (parameter file) for setting the database initialization parameters. This PFILE is read at instance startup time to get specific instance characteristics. The PFILE is text based, and can be edited in an editor like vi on UNIX or Notepad on Windows. Any changes that were made in PFILE would only take effect when the database is restarted.

15. ✅ THE SPFILE

👉 (server parameter file) - SPFILE is a binary file that contains the same information as the old PFILE. SPFILE permits dynamic changes without requiring you to restart that instance.
------------------------------------------------------------
16. ROLE :

=> Grouping of Privileges:

👉 Roles allow you to group multiple privileges together. Instead of granting individual privileges to each user, you can grant a role that contains all the necessary privileges.

👉 Example / why we use:
Instead of granting individual privileges like SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, and DELETE on multiple tables to a user, you can create a role that includes these privileges and then grant the role to the user.
------------------------------------------------------------
17. PROFILE:

👉 Control Resource Usage:

Profiles allow administrators to set limits on how many amount of system resources a user can consume. This prevents any single user from monopolizing database resources, which can impact the performance of other users and applications.

✅ TYPES Of PROFILE -- 2 Types.

👉 Password Profile : User ke password-related policies control karta hai.

PASSWORD_LIFE_TIME
PASSWORD_GRACE_TIME -- after getting expired password how long user can login with that pass.
PASSWORD_REUSE_TIME
PASSWORD_REUSE_MAX
FAILED_LOGIN_ATTEMPTS
PASSWORD_LOCK_TIME
PASSWORD_VERIFY_FUNCTION

✅ Purpose ::

👉 Password expiry
👉 Account lock
👉 Password complexity
👉 Password reuse restriction


👉 Resource Profile : User kitne database resources use kar sakta hai, ye control karta hai.

SESSIONS_PER_USER
CPU_PER_SESSION
CPU_PER_CALL
CONNECT_TIME
IDLE_TIME
LOGICAL_READS_PER_SESSION
LOGICAL_READS_PER_CALL
PRIVATE_SGA

✅ Purpose :: 

👉 CPU limit
👉 Session limit
👉 Idle time limit
👉 Connect time limit
