23. What is FLASHBACK ? Types of FLASHBACK ?

👉 FLASHBACK is a oracle feature that helps to recover database object or database any past
point-in-time.

✅ Flashback ka Purpose : 
    
    Suppose mistakenly we drop/delete any database object, if Flashback is enable then
    we can recover that object.

✅ Types of Flashback : 3 Types. Flashback Table, Flashback Database, Flashback Transaction


👉 Flashback Table : table ko purane state me le jana. 
    -- FLASHBACK TABLE emp TO TIMESTAMP (SYSDATE - 1/24);

👉 Flashback Database : Puri database ko past time par le jana.
    -- FLASHBACK DATABASE TO TIMESTAMP TO_TIMESTAMP('2026-06-17 10:00:00','YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS');

👉 Flashback Transaction : To see Transaction history. Kis transaction ne kya changes kiye,
                            dekhne ke liye.
    -- SELECT * FROM FLASHBACK_TRANSACTION_QUERY;
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

